main event: On October 7, 1955, at the Cecil Castle County Airport in Elkton, Maryland, a cigar-shaped light estimated to be 125 feet in length was observed traveling at 200 mph in a straight and level flight path.
interesting points: The object was described as a bright fluorescence light resembling a long cigar, sharper at the front than the rear.
The duration of the sighting was 10-15 minutes with no visible course for the object.
The report indicates the presence of known aircraft in the area at the time of the sighting, suggesting the possibility of it being an aircraft.
Despite the presence of aircraft, the report concluded that there was insufficient data for evaluation.
The report contains the mention of 'Light agent activity during the reported sighting' and is classified as a 'Negative' report.
